headline: GDIT Awarded Mission Partner Environment Contract
summary: General Dynamics Information Technology (GDIT), a business unit of General Dynamics (NYSE:GD), announced today it was awarded a new $5.6 billion contract by the Air Force Mission Partner Capabilities Office. The single award, indefinite-delivery indefinite-quantity contract, awarded in November, has a five-year base period and a five-year option.

headline: Boeing Wins Order for up to 200 737 Max Jets From Pegasus Airlines
summary: BA secures a contract with Pegasus Airlines for 100 737-10 jets, with options for additional 100 jets.
